Camera Control






































 
Skip to content





















HomeProductsSolutionsHow to BuySupportUpcoming EventsNewsContact UsSearchIBC 2017




















Optional Camera Control

Experience Integrated Camera Control





			Fof 
			Sony, Panasonic, Vaddio, LUMEns, Hitachi, telemetrics and marshall robotic Cameras
			

			This must-have switcher option works with every Broadcast Pix system's integrated workflow to effortlessly extend operator control to up to 12 robotic cameras. See how easy it can be to showcase your talent or players from the best possible angle with Broadcast Pix camera control. 
			









                  






How Camera Control Can Benefit You!



Control with confidence: enjoy full movement control from any Broadcast Pix device 
Offers great flexibility: control any combination of robotic cameras without the need of additional equipment or support
Save money on production costs: automate your camera control without comprising quality
Great for any production: from large multi-camera events, like live sports broadcasts, to single camera productions 
Adds future proof technology 


			Control Your Show Cameras By:



			A Professional and Virtual Control Panel
			

			Choose to control your show cameras from any Broadcast Pix control 
			panel using our patented PixButtons and device controls. 

			PixButtons are 
			our dynamic LED displays that show the device or file name assigned it, 
			for maximum switching confidence. Your camera preset positions are 
			displayed across your PixButtons, providing fast-action control over up 
			to 100 different presets positions. PixButtons can also be used to set 
			the speed and movement range of camera panning and tilting. 

			Or if you 
			prefer manual control, rely the dedicated device control area of your 
			panel. Featuring a 3D joystick and knobs, you can manually control 
			almost every aspect of your selected camera including; pan, tilt, zoom, 
			focus, iris and white balance. 


			Multi-View or Touchscreen

			The multi-view display shows thumbnails of each camera preset position. These 
			thumbnails views provide quick and error 
			free camera selections.  In addition, the operator has course and fine 
			adjustment with variable acceleration for creating the perfect shot.
			

			Automation with Fluent Macros
			
			The Fluent Macros process of streamlining a series of switcher moves 
			into one simple step, can further simplify Broadcast Pix camera control.
			Easily incorporate camera moves with Broadcast Pix Fluent Macros and 
			automate your next production. 


			Enjoy integrated control of:







Sony Cameras 



				Control up to 12 robotic Sony cameras, each with 16 presets. 
Now featuring control for Sony IP-based ptz cameras including the BRC-Z330, the BRC-900 and the SRG-300 models. 


Panasonic Cameras




				Control up to 12 robotic Panasonic cameras, with up to 100 preset positions
Features support for the entire line of the Panasonic AW series  including the AW-HE100 and the AW-PH400.




Lumens Cameras


				Control up to 12 robotic Lumens cameras, each with 16 presets. 
Features support for a variety of Lumens cameras including the VC-G30SU, the VC-A50S, the VC-G30 and the VC-G50.

Marshall Cameras


				Control up to 12 robotic Marshall cameras, each with 16 presets.



Vaddio Cameras




				Control up to 12 robotic Vaddio cameras. 
Features support for the RoboSHOT, ClearVIEW and PowerVIEW line of cameras.


Telemetrics Cameras




Control up to 10 Telemetrics Camera Systems including pan/tilt heads 
				and robotic equipment, pedestals and tracks.

Hitachi




				Control up to 9 robotic Hitachi cameras, each with 32 presets.
Features support of a wide-range of Hitachi Eagle Pan/Tilt Heads, including the 
				PT-101. 


			 
 
 
			






			To learn more about our robotic camera control, contact your local Broadcast Pix Dealer














 




