Broadcast Pix, Inc.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 2:23 PM ET
Media

Company Overview of Broadcast Pix, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Broadcast Pix, Inc. provides integrated live video production systems for broadcast, streaming, live event, and visual radio applications. It offers BPNet, a cloud-based IP workflow management solution for video production for its integrated production switchers. The company also provides Rapid CG software that offers an advanced tool for the creation of data-intensive CG graphics to its integrated production switchers. In addition, it offers slow motion sports replay systems, which include ReVue, a professional sports replay system; and PixPlay, a software option that allows integrated production switchers to provide slow motion control. Further, the company provides VOX, a software that au...
Broadcast Pix, Inc. provides integrated live video production systems for broadcast, streaming, live event, and visual radio applications. It offers BPNet, a cloud-based IP workflow management solution for video production for its integrated production switchers. The company also provides Rapid CG software that offers an advanced tool for the creation of data-intensive CG graphics to its integrated production switchers. In addition, it offers slow motion sports replay systems, which include ReVue, a professional sports replay system; and PixPlay, a software option that allows integrated production switchers to provide slow motion control. Further, the company provides VOX, a software that auto-detects which microphone is active, triggers a series of camera moves accordingly, and activates Fluent Macros assigned to that microphone. Its solutions are used to ingest various forms of content ranging from video and audio, data, or social media to delivery on air or to Web. The company serves broadcast stations, Internet broadcasters, production trucks, stadiums, staging companies, corporations, universities, houses of worship, and government studios internationally. It sells its products through dealers and distributors worldwide. Broadcast Pix, Inc. was founded in 2002 and is based in Billerica, Massachusetts. The company has additional offices in North America, Europe, and China.
Detailed Description


